Text: Careful, or you might slip and fall.
This is no time for sightseeing, my friend.
Did the heretics make camp here?
If they did, they have long since fled.
Surely, the beast is no match for my fire.
Thal's bloody balls, all that ice...
I feared I'd slip and break my neck.
Did that goobbue just jump out of a snowball?
Where did it even come from?
Why must the heretics reside in such bitter climes?
Chin up, friend. Try to think of this as field training... Extreme field training.
Hacking through all that fur won't be easy.
If anyone can pierce that thick hide, it's you.
A snowball fight is not what I was expecting...
I'll have to remember not to underestimate yetis in future.
We must stop the archbishop before it's too late!
Aye. But nevertheless, we were victorious.
Perhaps there's a secret passage here somewhere.
Surely, there's a passage through somewhere.
We need but fight our way through, then?
We must be careful. I sense a foul aether in the air.
Would you look at the size of that wolf!
The legendary hoarhound... This is not a foe to be trifled with.
Hmmm. This scaffolding seems sturdy enough.
Curious how the crystal has grown around the debris.
Let's hope there's a clear path up to the top of the wreckage.
What will we find in here, I wonder?
Is that...a bird? It only has one leg.
Something tells me there are more nearby...
I fear we've more than its one leg to worry about.
For a moment there, I thought they might blow us from the hull.
I dare not ask how they learned to use explosives like that.
Imperials. I had hoped we could avoid them, alas.
Look there. I think that inductor is powering the barrier.
I like not the looks of that inductor. Best we get rid of it.
Well, I certainly wasn't expecting a gunship.
I'm beginning to grow tired of being struck from the sky...
Come what may, you'll not want for succor.
I thought it would prove more of a challenge than that.
I pray that was the last of the imperials.
Did I burn it down too quickly for your liking?
Hold on, everyone. We're nearly there.
Are we almost there? I fear my legs may give out soon.
Sounds to me like you need a tougher training regimen.
Even should our enemy be a great wyrm, we mustn't falter!
That we should do battle with a great wyrm...
Let us show him the strength of mortal will!
I feel I've seen this plant's like before, but where...?
Here to delay us, no doubt.
Focus on cutting down the plants. I'll provide support.
There's no time. We must force our way through them!
I didn't come all this way to cut down overgrown weeds...
Nevertheless, I would see if your lance is suited to the task.
They would turn the Vault itself against us?
We've still a long way to go.
Still no sign of the archbishop.
Stop! We did not come here to do battle.
Forgive me, but we have to defend ourselves.
Must we always resort to violence?
We must slay or be slain. Make your choice.
Its scales are like unto armor.
A thick hide will not spare it from my lance.
I'd expect nothing less from the Vault's defenses.
Hmph, it was a worthy adversary.
We are not here for you to enjoy sport, dragoon.
A knight of the Heavens' Ward!?
Please, I beg you─let us pass!
Your words fall on deaf ears.
If you would flee, now is the time.
And abandon our mission? Don't be absurd.
I like not the sound of that thunder.
These lightning strikes... Are they the work of dragons?
Never mind that. We have to hurry.
Your lightning won't save you now.
By the gods, we did it!
This is no time to celebrate─we must keep moving.
Even so, we must remain calm.
They'll not defeat us through sheer numbers.
Aye, let us show them the futility of brute force!
This one appears stronger than the others, but it matters little.
This one appears stronger than the others, but it matters little.
I leave the vanguard to you.
Nidhogg is close. I sense him.
We must rout them quickly, ere they overwhelm us.
How did he transform into that monstrosity?
I fear we have little time to ruminate. Come, my friends!
Ser Grinnaux. I should have known you would be here.
You bested him once before. Together, we shall do so again.
His title as a knight of the Heavens' Ward is well earned.
You fought well, my friend, but our mission is far from over.
He means to escape by airship?
Do not be disheartened, my friends. We must give it our all!
I shall carve a path forward!
I am of the first brood!
Let me to do my part.
We shall see whose rage is the greater!
Quite literally a twisted place, the void.
Stay focused. Voidsent could be anywhere.
Those ones appear to be sentries.
Guarding the dungeon, I shouldn't doubt.
Is she the mistress of the castle!?
Whoever she is, we'll tend to her like the rest.
Well fought, my friends. Let us press on.
As grand a castle as any I've seen.
If the mistress is here, we must repay her earlier kindness.
The woman in the painting─do you suppose...?
Aye, I suspect it's the mistress in bygone days.
I sense potent magicks from her. Have care.
Hmph, she's quick on her feet if nothing else.
She may still be a threat. After her.
Do voidsent appreciate flowers too, I wonder...
I sense something sinister in the air...
It seems he wants to devour us too.
That must be the castle proper. Not too shabby.
Grrr, why are you still alive!?
Servants of the gods... I leave them in your hands!
Ice sculptures? Nay, they're more servants!
None the worse for the wear, I hope?
Such a grueling trial that was.
Only one other divinity would abide in the Heaven of Ice...

Where is I...?
Who am this place...?

Ziggy biggie pretties time!
Ziggy Ziggy hey!

Ziggy super beam time!
Ziggy Ziggy hey!
These eggs belong to these ones now!
Now walking ones know how these ones feel!
Uwaaah, slimy ones are too slimy!
This one is tired! Walking ones are not forgiven...but these ones are going home!
Th-That was amazing! I've never felt so exhilarated in my life! <wheeze>
I shall see these eggs safely to Gridania. Let us meet anon!
This one is tired of pilfering pranks─too easy!
Tee hee! These eggs are so shiny and nice!
I underestimated our foe. Retreat, tonberry! Retreat!

Serves walking ones right!
Victory for these ones!
ErRoR. uNaBlE tO dIfFeReNtIaTe FrIeNd FrOm FoE.

RePlEnIsHiNg AeThErIc StOrEs...
PrEpArInG fOr CoMbAt...

Nooo! Nooo!
This egg belongs to this one!

Waaaaaah! <sob>
This one wants mother one!
Walking ones will never have these eggs!
Hee hee! Try to take them, clumsy one!
This will teach meddling ones not to meddle!
I daresay we've collected a tonberry's dozen! <snort> Shall we make our way back, or have you gathered more?
You need to be quicker than that!
Ah, visitors! How refreshing! I am the caretaker of this facility, and it is my pleasure to receive you─albeit in an incorporeal form.
You are extraordinary familiars indeed to have endured the trials thus far. This calls for a reward. I do hope you'll like it.

My, what curious
familiars you are!
Let's play a game! Defeat me, and I'll give you a reward!
What's wrong? You're running out of time!
You'd better hurry or I'll get away!

It's as if I'm not even here...
I've had enough, I'm leaving!
That's the spirit! But can you keep it up?
You'll need to do better if you want your prize!

Oh, what a shame!
Better luck next time!
Even warmachina seem to love me.
And I was just getting started...
What a gentlemanly duo we are!♪
In the name of the Fury!
As long as I can hold a shield!

You must do better
than that against me!
Even at a glance, I see many interesting tomes.
'Tis a pity they had to be abandoned.
Is that supposed to be a grimoire!?
Yes, but not the kind you want to read, ribbit.
Is that a treatise on the New World I spy?
Ah yes, I've read that one. I can recommend it.
The entrance to the forbidden section is just ahead, ribbit.
Which makes this fellow here the gatekeeper.
I wouldn't have guessed it weak to fire.
On account of being bound to a tome, I would assume.
An arcane entity that can summon familiars!
The guardians of the forbidden section are a class apart.
Forbidden tomes can certainly assume many forms...
Master Matoya's tome is at the far end, ribbit.
Did you ever doubt it? Come, let's finish this.
Falling rocks to add to the danger...
Falling rocks to add to the danger...
We can't lower our guard even in battle.
Is that a balloon on his back!?
Is that a balloon on his back!?
Be on guard for attacks from above!
His tactics were unique to say the least...
His tactics were unique to say the least...
Their mastery of the wind isn't to be scoffed at.
An impressive feat, I must allow.
How did they acquire the technology?
Does she mean to rouse the wind with that fan!?
Does she mean to rouse the wind with that fan!?
The knights of our camp have just the defense!
I daresay she was one of the Galeborne.
<pant> Her attacks were a veritable storm...
I daresay she was one of the Galeborne.
A pity my arrows can't pierce them...
We're well and truly in the sky now.
We're well and truly in the sky now.
I can't be back on solid ground soon enough...
Let us prove our worth, my friends!
Aye, beyond a shadow of doubt!
By the Twelve, it's Chieftain Moglin!
That he should be part of the trial...
I didn't expect to face the moogles...
I pray they aren't too badly hurt.
<pant> The air is rather thin this high up...
It isn't a race, so let us pace ourselves.
The wyrm depicted on yonder crest...
Neither Hraesvelgr nor Nidhogg. It could only be Ratatoskr.
A winged horse...and an enormous one at that!
There isn't much room to maneuver. Have care!
That creature was truly fearsome in motion...
Thankfully we managed to rein it in.
Good heavens, what a majestic place...
I daresay we are come to Ratatoskr's sanctuary.
We will win you over, Hraesvelgr. Mark my words.
All that I have, I shall bring to bear!
Not foes to be trifled with, Garleans...
Aye, this is one battle we can't afford to lose!
The wall seems to go on forever...
Seems there's fewer of them this way.
That's no armor I've seen before...
That's no armor I've seen before...
Right, the outer reaches are just ahead.
We must stay on our toes.
Right, the outer reaches are just ahead.
Is that the switch for the platform?
It seems we must ride this platform.
Is that the switch for the platform?
Only one way to find out.
Ugh, if I never see another magitek weapon...
Ugh, if I never see another magitek weapon...
Sorry to disappoint, but I think there's more.
Worry not, I'll tend your wounds!
I could've done without the swarm of little ones.
I could've done without the swarm of little ones.
There's fighting over on the other side as well.
You can't fool us with those uniforms!
If they're here, then that means...
The Griffin finally shows his face!
We won't let you cause any more harm!
The Griffin finally shows his face!
Your scheming ends here, you bastard!
An aetherial path... No simple thing to create.
By the Twelve, it's literally upside down!
The aether is so dense as to be blinding.
Good gods, what an enormous poroggo!
They must provide excellent board here.
I pray I never hear that song again...
Right, into the aether we go.
Is this it, then? The aetherial sea?
This is the shore, you might say.
We'll deal with them like the rest.
I imagine they were drawn to the crystals.
That was tougher than I expected...
Even the candles burn upside down...
How very Sharlayan to obsess over useless details.
Defenses for the innermost sector, eh?
Can't lower our guard even for a moment!
Those dolls are the guardians of the viewing chamber?
Have care─I sense tremendous power from them!
These old limbs are limbered up!
This place just keeps getting weirder...
Just about everything is lit up in here.
This place just keeps getting weirder...
If it isn't an imperial legatus!
If it isn't an imperial legatus!
At least he knows when to quit.
It seems he wasn't here for us.
What the hells is that sphere?
I don't like the looks of those tanks...
What do you suppose are in those tanks?
What a strange-looking...I'm going to go with “thing.”
Whatever that thing is, it isn't what it seems!
Never fought anything like that before.
Certainly an efficient way to test creations...
Wonder where this will take us.
How vast could this facility possibly be?
I swear, every time you ride a lift...
I swear, every time you ride a lift...
Oh, that enormous sphere just screams “evil.”
What could that illuminated place be?
What could that illuminated place be?
The beating heart of aetherochemistry, perhaps...
Here is where the path ends, it seems.
Looks like this is as deep as it goes.
Looks like this is as deep as it goes.
We won't let you do as you please!
We'll teach you to underestimate us!
It seems we were right to ride atop the snowcraft.
The wildlife here is certainly bold.
It seems we were right to ride atop the snowcraft.
Indeed. Let us hold nothing back.
White as far as the eye can see...
I imagine the view from here must be breathtaking.
You can see the Tower of Babil from here!
You can see the Tower of Babil from here!
And it's no less imposing, even from this great distance.
If this beast would bar our path...
Is this beast native to the mountain?
A veritable giant among the wildlife here to be sure.
If this beast would bar our path...
There is something to be said for the fortitude of nature.
How vast is this cavern, I wonder?
Is it just me, or is the wind blowing warm air?
This is no time for gawping. Watch your step.
The presence of voidsent permeates this place...
The reaper village. Or what remains of it...
Is this the village Jullus told us about?
The presence of voidsent permeates this place...
I would expect no less from the birthplace of the reaper's art.
Despite their menacing demeanor, they're quite charming.
What possessed them to create such automata?
And equipped for combat training. How delightful...
That doll was not unlike a voidsent...
At the very least, it made for good sport.
That doll was not unlike a voidsent...
We can muse about that later. Let's get going.
Azdaja! I sense she is close!
So the gate really was here.
This one's not at all like the others.
An archfiend... So this is Golbez's doing.
It looks a lot like the Kojin.
No doubt it is here to guard the gate.
To be appointed as an archfiend, I should certainly think so.
It will take more than that to stop us.
Were I to chart our course...
The portal, if you would, good sir.
Seal of shadow, reveal thy path!
Excellent! Let us be about it.
There is no end to these beasts!
'Tis little wonder the mount was sealed.
No! My climbing attire is soaked...
Oh dear. They've raided the place!
Gods, they're everywhere! Have at them!
Oho! The wicked presence is no more.
All this for a dead end...? How odd.
You mean to take to the roof!?
I see the mononoke share your sensibilities!
Let us head back inside, quickly!
That battle must have blown out the lights.
Another flight of stairs! Shall we?
I shall leave the martial matters to you!
I spy a structure in the distance...
So many horrors, so little time!
Why, I feared that would be the end of me!
This temple is the pinnacle of picturesque.
Nooo! Spare me, I beg of you!
That way! Oh yes, that way!
How dare you! How dare you!
Would that we had a bit more light.
“Be careful what you wish for,” and all that...
I see naught else of note here.
Might I suggest you take this elsewhere!?
I would prefer not to join the fray, thank you!
No time to tarry! We've a ways to go.
I believe this is where you come in!
What lies at the end of the path, I wonder...?
There's a veritable menagerie on this mountain!
And just like that, the scenery is ruined!
You would think they'd have given up by now...
Hmm... Where to go from here?

Pray go on ahead...
I need a moment.
...This is precisely why a life of adventure is not for me.
'Tis as though it's answering! How very polite.
The result of a landslide, perhaps?
A shinobi? And out in the open, at that...
What is that lodged in the statue?
That pillar of light... Is it a geyser?
The isle proper is within sight.
That building certainly looks the part.
A Sharlayan facility, and no mistake.
It seems we will not pass here without a struggle.
Lyngbakr, dread beast of the seas.
It cometh as no surprise that the vegetation here is eminently lush.
A convenient mode of transport, that.
Such lines are installed throughout the isle, I believe.
The isle hath effected a curious change upon yonder golems.
There's such a thing as too much aether.
Is that bear from the ice field?
That aether should crystallize upon its very body...
Doesn't look like the type to welcome houseguests.
Drawn hither by the profusion of aether, I daresay.
No small amount of lightning it harbored.
Just another beast in the end.
Such an overwhelming concentration of aether!
We are come close enough to see even the finer movements of aether.
I suppose we aim for that massive geyser?
Though not for want of trying, I suspect.
That was rather too high for comfort, I must confess...
There'll be nothing left of you but a smoking crater!
Look upon a samurai of Doma!
By the blessing of the land!
Ugh... Weak as a spent steed...
Grass that is trampled grows back stronger!
The weave of a shinobi's power!
I hope you like it rough.
Feel the might of the Kraken!
Nothing's going to stop us from getting to the Far East!
I'll not suffer troublemakers aboard my ship.
Nothing's going to stop us from getting to the Far East!
I shudder to imagine what awaits here...
If we can punch them, we can deal with them!
Far from it. Whatever brought us here wouldn't fall so easily.
S-So long as my spells work...
It appears to have been adrift for a while.
And so it shouldn't. Ghosts are but men trapped in purgatory.
It appears this was a prison isle.
I daresay we will soon meet our host.
I daresay we will soon meet our host.
So this is the source of the legend.
Is that the ghost of a siren!?
Is that the ghost of a siren!?
And the source of the legend, 'twould seem.
So this is the hero's path... Let's prove ourselves worthy!
This day, we shall be warriors born anew!
Nice of them to afford us the chance to limber up.
There is no telling what awaits. Let us remain vigilant.
It appears these beasts are our next test.
No mistaking who the leader is.
That fellow knew how to charge...
Aye, a warrior in its own right.
That such a place should exist in the Steppe!
You truly get the sense that this is sacred ground.
Indeed! Gives me chills just to be here!
The stone is alive! What sorcery is this!?
Are those seals or hammers in its hands?
Whew, such a scramble that was...
Is it over...? My head's spinning something fierce.
It seems that was a test of judgment in the heat of battle.
After that dip, I'm glad for the warmth of the torches.
A cavern now... This is turning out to be quite a tour.
A cavernous space behind a portentous gate... This ought to be good!
I daresay we are come to the yol's nest!
'Twould seem we've reached the path's end.
This is it, my friends─the final test!
All who bar our way shall taste my steel!
I am Gosetsu, samurai of Doma─
Now is not the time to be announcing yourself!
Metal toys will not stop us!
Metal toys will not stop us!
My blade will make short work of this!
This appears to be the guardian of the gate!
This appears to be the guardian of the gate!
Is that your idea of an ambush?
Is that your idea of an ambush?
Ugh, I'm too old for this...
Another machina to reduce to scrap metal!
Unusual or no, it will fall all the same!
